Maybach Music Group executive, Rick Ross, has arrived Lagos for an Easter concert. The Nation sighted the rapper in a four- second video shared by a Twitter user. The rapper returned to Nigeria for the show tagged ‘Rick Ross Live In Lagos’ after his first trip in 2012. He had stormed Lagos for the Summer Jam Fest 2012 concert.   Marriage not ticket to financial freedom – Didi Ekanem     Nigerian artistes very similar to politicians –…     It’s time 2Baba gets vasectomy – Shade Ladipo   He also seized the opportunity to shoot an alternate video for his ‘Hold Me Back’ song which immediately went viral. He took to a slum in Lagos where he was seen spraying kids dollars. Popular music duo, P Sqaure featured him during the same period for ‘Beautiful Onyinye’ remix. ‘Rick Ross Live In Lagos’ taking place Thursday (today) at Eko Hotel and Suites will feature popular artistes including Davido, Tiwa Savage, Mayorkun, DJ Obi, The Cavemen, Fave, and DJ Yin among others